us language. Featuring a new foreword, Theology and the Scientific Imagination is a pathbreaking and classic work that remains a fundamental resource for historians and philosophers of science.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGodxAttributesxHistory of doctrines. 0aKnowledge, Theory ofxHistory. 0aPhilosophyxHistory. 0aReligion and science. 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh  aCatholic.  aChristian theology.  aDescartes.  aEnlightenment.  aGiambattista Vico.  aGod's will.  aGod.  aHenry More.  aKarl Marx.  aLeibniz.  aMalebranche.  aMiddle Ages.  aSpinoza.  aabsolute autonomy.  aactual beings.  aanti-religious.  aautonomy.  adivine knowledge.  adivine omnipotence.  adivine providence.  adoing.  aeternal truths.  agoodness.  ahuman history.  ahuman knowledge.  ainvisible-hand.  aknower.  aknowing.  aknowledge.  aknown.  alaymen.  amankind.  amedieval philosophers.  amedieval theology.  amodern science.  anature.  aphilosophy.  apower.  areason.  asavants.  ascientific revolution.  ascientific thinking.  asecular theologians.  asecularization.  aseventeenth-century thinkers.  asocial nature.  asociety.  atheology.  atruth.1 aSheehan, Jonathan.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831106633650 cprintz978069118135640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691184265?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691184265423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691184265/original  a978-3-11-066336-5  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  